article.headline: Kennesaw State 75, Stetson 59
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- Markeith Cummings scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Kennesaw State to a 75-59 win over Stetson on Sunday. Cummings connected on 6 of 12 from the field as the Owls (8-12, 3-6 Atlantic Sun Conference) shot 53.2 percent (25 of 47). Kurtis Woods added 13 points for Kennesaw State and LaDaris Green and Jon-Michael Nickerson chipped in 11 each. Two 3-pointers by Cummings and a three-point play by Kelvin McConnell gave the Owls a 24-13 lead with 9:38 left in the first half. The Hatters cut it to 24-19 on back-to-back 3's by A.J. Smith and Mark Lohuis. But Stetson wouldn't get within single digits the rest of the way, as Kennesaw State scored seven straight. Smith finished with 17 points and Ridge Graham added 15 points for the Hatters (5-13, 3-7).
